## ARTICLE I: Company Formation and Purpose
 
### 1.1 Formation
The Member has formed a Limited Liability Company under the laws of the State of North Dakota by filing the Articles of Organization with the Secretary of State.
 
### 1.2 Name
The name of the Company shall be abcAssess LLC. The business of the Company may be conducted under that name or any other name chosen by the Member.
 
### 1.3 Business Purpose
The primary purpose of the Company is to design, develop, host, market, and manage the educational assessment software application known as abcAssess, including its web and mobile iterations, and to engage in any other lawful business activities permitted within the State.
 
### 1.4 Principal Place of Business
The location of the principal place of business of the Company shall be: 3306 Belmont Road, Grand Forks, ND 58201. The Member may change the location of the principal place of business at any time.
 
> *Attorney note: Consider updating to a PO Box or virtual office address to keep home address out of public business records.*
 
### 1.5 Registered Agent
The name and address of the Company's registered agent for service of process in the State of North Dakota shall be: Danielle Andrist, 3306 Belmont Road, Grand Forks, ND 58201.
 
> *Attorney note: Consider using a professional registered agent service (~$50-100/year) to avoid using home address in public records. Update this section if a registered agent service is used.*
 
### 1.6 Intellectual Property Ownership
All work product, source code, design assets, trademarks, trade secrets, and improvements created, developed, or acquired in connection with the business of the Company — whether by the Member, the Manager, or any contractor, employee, or third party engaged by the Company — shall be and remain the sole and exclusive property of the Company. Any contractor or third party engaged by the Company shall be required to execute a written assignment of intellectual property rights prior to the commencement of work.
 
### 1.7 Personal License-Back to Member
 
Notwithstanding Section 1.6, the Company hereby grants to the Member a non-exclusive, royalty-free, perpetual, worldwide license to reference, describe, display, and discuss the Company's intellectual property, products, and the Member's role in their creation for the following personal, non-competing purposes:
 
(a) inclusion in the Member's personal portfolio, resume, curriculum vitae, or professional biography;
 
(b) use in speaking engagements, panels, interviews, podcasts, conference presentations, or educational instruction, including the Member's planned early childhood conference presentations;
 
(c) use in articles, case studies, or educational content authored by the Member describing her experience building and operating the Company; and
 
(d) any other use reasonably related to the Member's professional development, personal brand, or career advancement.
 
This license does not permit the Member to disclose the Company's proprietary source code, confidential trade secrets, or non-public financial information, and does not grant any right to compete with the Company, to commercialize a substantially similar product, or to use Company trademarks in a manner likely to cause confusion as to the source of competing goods or services. This license survives any sale, transfer, or dissolution of the Company, and survives the Member's departure from any future management or ownership role, provided such departure was not the result of a breach of this Agreement, fraud, or willful misconduct by the Member.
 
